org.jsapar.parse

Interface ParseTask

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractParseTask, BeanParseTask, TextParseTask, XmlParseTask

    public interface ParseTask
    Common interface for all parse jobs. The interface does not state anything about the origin of the parsed items. An instance of a parser is only useful once. You create an instance, initializes it with the event listeners needed, then call execute().
    See Also:
    TextParseTask, BeanParseTask

    • Method Detail

      • setLineEventListener

        void setLineEventListener(LineEventListener eventListener)
        Sets a line event listener to this parser. If you want more than one line event listener registered, use a MulticastLineEventListener.
        Parameters:
        eventListener - The line event listener.

      • setErrorEventListener

        void setErrorEventListener(ErrorEventListener errorEventListener)
        Sets an error event listener to this parser. Default behavior otherwise is to throw an exception upon the first error. If you want more than one listener to get each error event, use a MulticastErrorEventListener.
        Parameters:
        errorEventListener - The error event listener.

      • execute

        long execute()
      throws IOException
        Start the parsing. Should only be called once for each ParseTask. Consecutive calls may have unexpected behavior.
        Returns:
        Number of line events that were generated, i.e. the number of lines parsed.
        Throws:
        IOException - In case there is an error reading the input.
